  "contentPages" : [ 
  
  "The magnitude on which the ideals of the Terrene Protectorate had an influence on the Aureate Brotherhood and vice versa is yet to be fully grasped; ideas of unity for Glitchkind are commonly adopted by many Protectors at the academy, most of the time without knowing these ideas traces back to the collaboration between the first Protectors and the last Aureate priests and followers, all during the first hundred years of the Terrene Protectorate.",

"The Aureate Brotherhood precedes the Protectorate by 200 years approximately; not much is known about this era other than they were formed to study an enigmatic artifact they labeled as The Regal Medallion. They travelled to many Glitch kingdoms across the stars, realizing that the Glitch was a fragmented species, with kingdoms far away from each other, unaware of each other's existence.",

"At the point they joined the Protectorate, the Brotherhood was already on its mission to achieve unity and peace for all Glitch. The Brotherhood was important in the first Hermes missions led by the Astraeus Program, and the awareness of Glitch as a species scattered throughout space is the result of their efforts. Sadly, with years of persecution and the destruction of their major temple, the Brotherhood dissolved, with only the echoes of their ideals surviving nowadays."

